FBIS3-56937 "drsov014_a_94010" FBIS-SOV-94-014 Document Type:Daily Report 21 Jan 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Foreign Ministry Official Karasin Holds Briefing Kiev To Be Compensated for Nuclear Charges LD2001165094 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1600 GMT 20 Jan 94 LD2001165094 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Grigoriy Karasin, Russian Foreign Ministry's official representative, has confirmed that Moscow will provide Ukraine with fuel elements for the needs of atomic power engineering as a compensation for the nuclear charges that are being withdrawn. Speaking at a briefing in Moscow he added that the purchase by the United States of a part of the uranium released during the dismantling of nuclear weapons would contribute to solving the financial issues that emerge in this context.
